Interface GridImporter

    XMLGridImporter

    public interface GridImporter
    Imports a Grid from a File or a String.

    • Method Detail

      • importFromFile

        Grid importFromFile(java.io.File file)
        Imports a grid from a given File. This will not set the correct Class for the grid. This should be handled elsewhere.
        Parameters:
        file - a file that contains the Grid.
        Returns:
        New instance of a Grid from the source, or null if the import has failed.

      • importFromStream

        Grid importFromStream(java.io.InputStream inputStream)
        Imports a grid from a given input stream.
        Parameters:
        inputStream - an input stream that contains the Grid;
        Returns:
        New instance of a Grid from the source, or null if the import has failed.

      • importWithVehicleClass

        Grid importWithVehicleClass(java.io.File file,
                            VehicleClassLibrary library)
        Imports a grid from a given File and generates a new VehicleClass if a vehicle class is not present in the given VehicleClassLibrary. This will set the VehicleClass of Grid.
        Parameters:
        file - a file that contains the Grid.
        library - Vehicle Class Library that is meant to contain the newly loaded VehicleClass.
        Returns:
        New instance of a Grid from the source, or null if the import has failed.
